Paper: hep-th/9604001

Date: 1996-04-01

Title: C-theorem for two dimensional chiral theories

Authors: Fiorenzo Bastianelli and Ulf Lindstrom

Comments: 7 pages, uses harvmac.tex

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B380 (1996) 341-345

We discuss an extension of the $C$-theorem to chiral theories. We show thattwo monotonically decreasing $C$-functions can be introduced. However, theirdifference is a constant of the renormalization group flow. This constantreproduces the 't Hooft anomaly matching conditions.